BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:DAW-Y0CrtkKnILlcD2_Fw
SUMMARY:History Café: Preserving the Vision of Asahel Curtis
DTSTAMP:20260413T004138Z
DTSTART:20260415T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Margaret Weatherbee\\\, Head of Collections at the Washing
	ton State Historical Society and History Museum\\\, for an in-depth look a
	t the digitization and preservation of the Asahel Curtis Collection. This 
	collection features over 42\\\,000 images by photographer Asahel Curtis (1
	873-1941) that document the evolution of life in the Pacific Northwest in 
	the early 20th century. \\nHistory Café is produced as a partnership betwe
	en HistoryLink\\\, The Pacific Northwest Historians Guild\\\, and MOHAI. \
	\nASL Interpretation and CART captioning are available during the program.
	 In addition\\\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are avail
	able upon request. For more accessibility support\\\, email programs@mohai
	.org before the program. \\nGrab some food for thought–complimentary snack
	s and beverages will be provided. \\nIf you can’t make it to the museum\\\
	, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to virtually attend this event
	.\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-preserving-the-vision-of-asahel-
	curtis/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-preserving-the-vision-of-asahel-cu
	rtis/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\
	\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
